Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Instance 1: Constructs Involved: Plan Journey, Validate Route Availability, include (Plan Journey → Validate Route Availability)
   Instance 1: Explanation: "Validate Route Availability" is an inclusion use case included only by "Plan Journey". It is not associated with any actor, is not included by any other use case, does not include or extend any use case, is not extended by any use case, and has no generalization relationships. It represents a decomposed sub-step (checking if a route exists) rather than a complete, independently valuable service observable to a user. This is functional decomposition of "Plan Journey" into an artificially separated fragment.

